<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="B1" checkit-title="Types of Variables">
  <statement>
      
      
      
      
      
      <p>
          For each of the following, classify the type of variable described as <em>Numerical</em> or <em>Categorical</em>, as well as the subcategory <em>Continuous</em>, <em>Discrete</em>, <em>Nominal</em> or <em>Ordinal</em>.  Be sure to justify your choices.
          <ol>
              <li>The species of a bird observed on a hike.</li>
              <li>The species of termites infesting a house.</li>
              <li>The population of deer in a national park.</li>
              <li>The frequency a family does groccery shopping over the last month with groups defined 0-1, 2-5, 6-10, 11+.</li>
              <li>The frequency of wolf attacks on a rancher's herd in attacks/week.</li>
              <li>A choice of transportation (air, freight etc.).</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      
      
      
      
     <p>
          <ol>
              <li>Categorical, Nominal</li>
              <li>Categorical, Nominal</li>
              <li>Numerical, Discrete</li>
              <li>Categorical, Ordinal</li>
              <li>Numerical, Continuous</li>
              <li>Categorical, Nominal</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
          
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
